Variability of males.
Length: 16.1–17.5 mm. Parameres in dorsal view with the marked angle at the level of the central opening more or less developed (
Figs. 21, 22
), internal piece also variable (
Figs. 25, 26
).

Females of the two species show very moderate differences in the genital sclerites (
Figs. 27–30
), whose diagnostic value should be verified on a longer series.
